Local news outlets are reporting on President Biden's efforts to strengthen retirement savings, create jobs through the Bipartisan Infrastructure Law, and recognize exceptional individuals. In Ohio, President Biden announced the American Rescue Plan's Special Financial Assistance program, which aims to protect workers and retirees from pension cuts. The President also awarded the Presidential Medal of Freedom to individuals who have made significant contributions to the United States and the world. Furthermore, the Bipartisan Infrastructure Law is being highlighted for its investment of almost $1 billion in 85 airports across the country, aiming to improve customer experiences, boost the economy, and enhance competitiveness.